cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.MA, cs.SY

This paper discusses the design and implementation of Low Power Wide Area (LPWA) networks, which are primarily used for Internet of Things (IoT) applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the standardization activities carried out by different organizations, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of LPWA technologies for smart city and machine-to-machine (M2M) applications, which falls under the category of cs.COMM (Communication and Networking). The paper also discusses the challenges and potential directions for LPWA technologies, which falls under the category of cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
